This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump on July 7, 2019. The President discussed various topics, including the strong economic numbers of the United States, congratulating the women's soccer team on winning the World Cup, Iran's decision to start enriching uranium, the British ambassador's comments, the census, border conditions, and the New York Times' reporting on migrant detention centers. He also mentioned the possibility of inviting the women's soccer team to the White House and discussed China and the Federal Reserve.